sequenceDiagram
    participant A as Ansible (host)
    participant CP as cp1 (control plane)
    participant K as kubelet
    participant API as kube-apiserver
    participant Op as Tigera Operator
    participant Cal as calico-node

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
    Note over A,CP: Phase 2 — Ansible Setup
    A->>CP: ansible all -m ping
    CP-->>A: pong (SSH verified)
    end

    rect rgb(245, 255, 245)
    Note over A,Cal: Phase 3 — Control Plane Bootstrap
    A->>CP: kubeadm init --pod-network-cidr=192.168.0.0/16
    CP->>CP: Generate certs, write static pod manifests
    CP->>K: kubelet detects manifests in /etc/kubernetes/manifests/
    K->>K: Start etcd, apiserver, scheduler, controller-manager
    K->>API: Register node (NotReady — no CNI)
    API-->>A: kubeadm init complete
    A->>CP: Copy admin.conf → ~/.kube/config
    A->>CP: kubeadm token create --print-join-command
    CP-->>A: Save join command locally
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 238)
    Note over A,Cal: Phase 4 — Calico CNI
    A->>API: kubectl create tigera-operator.yaml
    API->>Op: Operator pod starts
    Op->>API: Register CRDs (Installation, etc.)
    A->>API: kubectl create custom-resources.yaml
    API->>Op: Installation CR detected
    Op->>Cal: Deploy calico-node DaemonSet
    Cal->>K: Assign pod CIDR to node
    K->>API: Update node status → Ready
    API->>API: Schedule CoreDNS pods
    Note over CP: cp1 is Ready, all system pods Running
    end
